commitResults.messageTitle: Update readme to reflect new IntelliJ version

commitResults.messageBody: String greeting was added and printed
Customised greeting and exit to add a personal flavour
List class controls all list data, Main will call on List to add and display list

- list class was revamped entirely
- removed excess import statements
- included validation check for done
- Trialed try-catch

- Some minor grammar edits
- Tweaked some UI prints to be consistent with the others
- Changed up "exit" to a softer "break" for "BYE" case.
- goodbye message now prints at the end of the program

commitResults.messageTitle: Removed List class and added Task class
commitResults.messageBody:
- Task class is a re-written List class
- Better user readability
- Cleaned up messy code

- Task is now inherited by Todo, Event, Deadline
- markDone is still under reformating

- Functionalities are as of level-4
- Added some new methods
- Removed input validation (for now)

commitResults.messageTitle: Added the header for the timestamp
commitResults.messageBody:
- Timestamps now have headers based on what the user inputs after the "/"
- Cleaned up messy code
